<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder12');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Western Animation&nbsp;</div><div id="folder12" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">
<ul><li> Eris from <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheGrimAdventuresOfBillyAndMandy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheGrimAdventuresOfBillyAndMandy">The Grim Adventures of Billy &amp; Mandy</a></em>, the goddess of chaos. Blonde and with a curvy body.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/StarWarsTheCloneWars" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/StarWarsTheCloneWars">Star Wars: The Clone Wars</a></em> has a woman known only as The Daughter, the physical embodiment of the light side of the Force. A slender beauty clad in <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoldAndWhiteAreDivine" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoldAndWhiteAreDivine">white and gold</a>, with an <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PhosphorEssence" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PhosphorEssence">angelic glow</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouGottaHaveBlueHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouGottaHaveBlueHair">green hair</a> that seems to float in the air behind her, and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbsoluteCleavage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbsoluteCleavage">Absolute Cleavage</a> on top of that.
</li><li> The Avatar on <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/AvatarTheLastAirbender" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/AvatarTheLastAirbender">Avatar: The Last Airbender</a></em> and <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheLegendOfKorra" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheLegendOfKorra">The Legend of Korra</a></em> tends to take the form of an attractive human. So far, all the known Avatars (Wan, Yangchen, Kuruk, Kyoshi, Roku <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IWasQuiteALooker" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IWasQuiteALooker">in his younger days</a>, Aang <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SheIsAllGrownUp" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SheIsAllGrownUp">as an adult</a>, and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoobsOfSteel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoobsOfSteel">Korra</a>) have all looked pretty damn good. The Painted Lady and <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Yue the moon spirit</span> could also be considered examples.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic">My Little Pony: Friendship Is Magic</a></em> - Princess Celestia is a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PhysicalGod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PhysicalGod">Physical God</a> who raises the sun. She's also drawn in such a way that indicates she is meant to be a radiant beauty among the pony folk.
<ul><li> Within the fandom, however, Princess Luna is typically considered the more beautiful of the two, which may partially be due to her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnsembleDarkhorse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnsembleDarkhorse">Ensemble Dark Horse</a> status.
</li></ul></li></ul></div>
<p></p><hr>
</div>
